---
// Milestone 3 review-gate landing page. Links to the design directions so the
// owner can compare them side by side before M4 builds the real theme.
// See MIGRATION_PLAN.md § "Milestone 3 — Two design directions". Direction C
// was added after initial feedback on A + B (see the M3 addendum in that
// file): B's colors/fonts + A's spacing/design, wider than both.
// Not a production route: excluded from sitemap.xml/feeds (which are
// hand-built from a fixed URL list, see src/pages/sitemap.xml.ts) and marked
// noindex below as a second layer of protection.
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
    <title>Milestone 3 — Design direction review</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        color-scheme: light dark;
        --bg: #ffffff;
        --fg: #16181d;
        --muted: #5b6270;
        --border: #dfe3e8;
        --surface: #f6f7f9;
      }

      @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
        :root {
          --bg: #14161a;
          --fg: #e9ebef;
          --muted: #9aa1ad;
          --border: #2b2f36;
          --surface: #1c1f24;
        }
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--fg);
        font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', system-ui, Roboto, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      .wrap {
        max-width: 880px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }

      p.lede {
        color: var(--muted);
        max-width: 68ch;
      }

      .directions {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        gap: 1.25rem;
        margin: 2.5rem 0;
      }

      .card {
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        background: var(--surface);
      }

      .card h2 {
        margin-top: 0;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
      }

      .card p {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
      }

      .card .links {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 1rem;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
      }

      .card .links a {
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .notes {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding-top: 1.5rem;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .notes li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }

      code {
        font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
        background: var(--surface);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
        border-radius: 0.25rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="wrap">
      <h1>Milestone 3 — Design direction review</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Three styled directions on the same real content — the home list and one full post
        (<code>2024-09-03-aspnetcore-options</code>, chosen for its code blocks and callouts).
        All three use a widescreen shell, a capped reading measure, an OS-aware light/dark toggle, and a
        documented set of color/type/spacing/radius tokens. Pick one (or ask for another blend) to move
        to Milestone 4, where it becomes the real theme.
      </p>

      <div class="directions">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>A — Restrained editorial</h2>
          <p>Serif headings over a sans body, generous whitespace, a single muted terracotta accent. Code sits quietly within the reading column.</p>
          <div class="links">
            <a href="/design-preview/a/">Home list →</a>
            <a href="/design-preview/a/post.html">Sample post →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>B — Technical / developer</h2>
          <p>All-sans, tighter type, a confident blue accent. Code blocks get terminal-style chrome and are allowed to run wider than the prose column.</p>
          <div class="links">
            <a href="/design-preview/b/">Home list →</a>
            <a href="/design-preview/b/post.html">Sample post →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>C — Editorial spacing, developer palette</h2>
          <p>A blend added after feedback on A + B: B's all-sans typefaces and blue/dark-terminal color palette, paired with A's generous spacing and quiet, near-flat component design — and the widest content area of the three.</p>
          <div class="links">
            <a href="/design-preview/c/">Home list →</a>
            <a href="/design-preview/c/post.html">Sample post →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ul class="notes">
        <li>Each direction has its own light/dark toggle (top right) — try both. The choice is remembered per-browser and shared across directions, so switching between them keeps whichever mode you picked.</li>
        <li>Links inside the rendered post body go to real production post URLs, which still use the Milestone 1 placeholder layout — that's expected, not a bug.</li>
        <li>Only the showcased post is wired to the full styled article view; the other titles on the home list are plain text for now.</li>
        <li>This page and everything under <code>/design-preview/</code> is a temporary review artifact (Milestone 3) — it is marked <code>noindex</code> and is not linked from the real site. It will be deleted once Milestone 4 builds the chosen theme.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
